Ettercap
Comprehensive suite for man-in-the-middle attacks

Sniffing & Spoofing
Description
Ettercap is a comprehensive suite for man-in-the-middle attacks. It features sniffing of live connections, content filtering, and many other interesting tricks. It supports active and passive dissection of many protocols.

Installation / Check
Check if installed:

which ettercap
Install command:

sudo apt install ettercap-graphical
Basic Syntax
ettercap -G (GUI) or ettercap -T (text)
Common Commands
Command	What it does	When to use	Risk
ettercap -G

Launch GUI - Opens graphical interface	For visual man-in-the-middle attacks	
ettercap -T -q -i eth0

Text mode quiet - CLI mode with minimal output	For headless systems	
ettercap -T -M arp:remote /192.168.1.1// /192.168.1.100//

ARP poisoning - MITM between two hosts	To intercept traffic between hosts	
ettercap -T -w capture.pcap -M arp:remote ///

Capture to file - Save intercepted traffic	To analyze traffic later	
Step-by-Step Guide
1
Launch ettercap: sudo ettercap -G
2
Select network interface
3
Scan for hosts: Hosts > Scan for hosts
4
Select targets from host list
5
Choose attack: Mitm > ARP poisoning
6
Start sniffing: Start > Start sniffing
7
View intercepted data in GUI
8
Stop attack when done
Understanding the Output
Ettercap shows intercepted packets, usernames/passwords from unencrypted protocols, and connection status. Successful ARP poisoning shows in the status bar.

